b'The Yuga Labs acquisition of CryptoPunks IP as a very positive outcome for CryptoPunks V1, as they have gone from the hands of a hostile founding company to a non-hostile acquirer.'

b'This means CryptoPunks V1 are almost certainly going to get added back to OpenSea, in the coming weeks which will almost certainly be extremely constructive for trade volume, and thus, the floor price.'
b'Yuga Labs has no intention or incentive to challenge the authenticity of V1 CryptoPunks as they have already stated they do not intend to follow up with the Larva Labs DMCA.'

b'CryptoPunks V1 has managed to for 4,651 ETH volume on Looksrare alone, and have managed to climb into the top 5 most traded NFT projects over the past week without being listed on the largest NFT exchange (OpenSea) AND with only ~2,200 total NFTs available and only 617 owners! https://t.co/lLPt0NaHrO'

b'The thesis for CryptoPunks V1 is that they are, without contention, the first pfp NFT collection in existence. So long as this does not change and there is no active campaign towards denying their authenticity, they should be of significant value to collectors.'

b"As for IP rights, I view this part of the equation as borderline irrelevant. Yuga Labs has set a strong precedent for giving IP rights to NFT holders, which is a good thing, but even if for some reason it was different for CryptoPunks V1 holders, I don't think it would matter."

b'This is being established as we speak for CryptoPunks V1 with many very large sales taking place (https://t.co/4HRoHdhatP), which will give collectors a stronger sense of confidence that these can hold their value.'
b'The main advantage V2 CryptoPunks currently have over V1s is the strong history of price appreciation and large sales which give buyers confidence.'

b'Given enough time, I strongly believe they will surpass the value of the V2 CryptoPunks as they are both older and rarer, making them more attractive to serious NFT collectors. Why spend hundred of thousands of dollars on something less rare and less historically significant?'

Apes flipping punks not only kicks cryptopunks from the # 1 spot
